To create a new project:
- create directory "development"
- create the angular project: ng new web-app
- npm install
    - may need to chmod 777 to the project if forking

For Python:
- cd into project root
- type: python app.py
- can hit rest services at: http://0.0.0.0:5000/angular-flask/service_name

For Angular:
- cd into development/web-app
- type: npm start
- app will load at: http://localhost:4200/

Required Software:
create node_modules folder in development/web-app/
- Xcode
    - from terminal run Xcode-select --install
- PIP
    - from terminal run sudo easy_install pip
- flask-cord
    - From terminal run pip install flask_cors
- @asymmetrik/ngx-leaflet
    - from terminal run npm install @asymmetrik/ngx-leaflet
    - copy @asymmetrik folder to development/web-app/node_modules
- leaflet.motion
    - rom terminal run npm install leaflet.motion
    - copy leaflet.motion folder to development/web-app/node_modules
- bootstrap
    - from terminal run npm install bootstrap
    - copy bootstrap folder to development/web-app/node_modules
- leaflet
    - rom terminal run npm install leaflet
    - copy leaflet folder to development/web-app/node_modules
- @types/leaflet
    - from terminal run npm install @types/leaflet
    - copy leaflet and geojson folders to your project development/node_modules/web-app/@types
- @elfalem/leaflet-curve
    - from terminal run npm install @elfalem/leaflet-curve
    - copy @elfalem folder to development/web-app/node_modules
- Font Awesome 5.13.0
    - download from https://fontawesome.com/download
    - Select “Free for Web”
    - Rename folder to font-awesome and copy it to development/web-app/node_modules




